<!doctype html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>InterMine Natural</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/bootstrap.css" />
        <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/natural.css" />

        <script>
        window.onerror = function(m, f, l) { (new Image).src = '/errors?message='+encodeURIComponent(m)+'&file='+encodeURIComponent(f)+'&line='+encodeURIComponent(l); }
        </script>
    </head>    
    <body>
        <div id="wrap" class="container">
            <header>
                <div id="logo"></div>
            </header>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="left span8">
                    <div class="content">
                        <div id="search">
                            <input type="text" class="input" />
                            <a class="btn btn-red" href="#">Search</a>
                        </div>

                        <div>
                            <div class="browse-categories">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <li>
                                            <a href="#">Company</a>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><a href="#">company (Class), department (Class), employee (Reference)</a></li>
                                                <li><a href="#">company (Class), employee (Reference)</a></li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </li>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="right span4">
                    <div class="content">
                        <div>
                            <div class="yellow-right-box">
                                <p>InterMine Natural is a semi-natural language user interface translating user's input into data warehouse model paths
                                    using <a href="http://www.swi-prolog.org/">SWI-Prolog</a>.</p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="brown-right-box">
                                <h2>How does it work?</h2>
                                <p>An input query is split into words that are passed into Prolog from CoffeeScript. Prolog tries to match each word to an end token, be it
                                    Class, Reference, Collection or an Attribute. Failing to match the whole sentence, each word is in turn replaced with a variable so that
                                    it can match any appropriate input. This process is repeated until we either get a model path match or we have exhausted all words
                                    from an input query.</p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="blue-right-box">
                                <h2>Get the source</h2>
                                <p>The source is GPL Licensed and can be had from its Bitbucket repository.</p>
                                <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#">Bitbucket</a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <footer>
                <p>
                    &copy; Radek Stepan 2012, <a>InterMine</a>
                </p>
            </footer>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>